                        in at least 4 manuscripts including <bibl type="syriaca:Manuscript" xml:id="witness2">ms Lady Meux6</bibl>.</note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1955-1">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1955">Pachomius</persName> is 
                        commemorated as one of the great founders of cenobitic monasticism whose rules for monastic communties had influence 
                        well beyond <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> where he founded <placeName>monasteries</placeName> for 
                        men and women.</note>
